ures decouple in the envelopes and that the dust grains are\nnot yet significantly coagulated. We observationally confirm chemical models of\nCO-freezeout and nitrogen chemistry. We find clear correlations between the\nhydrogen density and CO depletion and the emergence of N2H+. The chemical ages\nindicate a core lifetime of less than 1 Myr.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Aug 2013 19:52:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 12 Oct 2013 15:12:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-12-10"}
