of central galaxies to the red sequence increases by nearly\nan order of magnitude from z=1 to z=0. These results imply that the efficiency\nof quenching star formation for centrals is increasing with cosmic time, while\nthe mechanisms that quench the star formation of satellite galaxies in groups\nand clusters is losing efficiency.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Aug 2013 20:38:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
